        "id": 1128849
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T02:05:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The main functions are avcodec_decode_video2 for video decoding, and avcodec_decode_audio4 for audio. AVPacket is the data input, fetched from PacketQueue. When these two decode functions return, it will tell how much data has been decoded. If there are left overs, we will keep them into mTmpPkt, and continue to decode. got_frame is true is a whole frame is available, which may consume one or more packets. After decoding, the frame may contain a valid pts (presentation timestamp), if not, we call av_frame_get_best_effort_timestamp() to get one",
      "parentUuid": "dff39992_d0b504c8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 87,
