    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "db342528_471ae435",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T01:30:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "isn\u0027t it possible to call this from a different thread anyway? It seems less confusing on balance if we just call this decodeAudio and continue to let the decoder thread call this function.\n\nBest would be to pass a closure to the decoder thread so that it becomes a simple worker thread consuming work items that VideoPlayer produces.\n\nAs is, it can be confusing, at least for a non-ffmpeg wizard like me, to see how all the parts fit together and where each part is used. VideoPlayer and the packet queues seem to have a bunch of state that is used in many locations :/",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 95,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "854111173c42bec9e93fa3db0691749bfa79899a",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0ae75272_8d3b2b6e",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1128849
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T02:05:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is indeed the decoder thread. Decoder class does not launch any thread right now, it\u0027s a pure data keeping class, i.e., mThread in Decoder is no longer used. I moved it to this main class here, since it\u0027s more related to other stuff, such as frame queue, and timing info.",
      "parentUuid": "db342528_471ae435",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 95,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 35
      },
      "revId": "854111173c42bec9e93fa3db0691749bfa79899a",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d16ba2ca_17f984e8",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T02:28:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In that case, if Decoder is just keeping decoding-related data, and it still interacts closely with VideoPlayer through decodeAudio/decodeVideo I think it should be absorbed into VideoPlayer as a private struct, so we don\u0027t have to keep flipping between Decoder and VideoPlayer .cpp to see where things actually happen.\n\nWe can either inline all the Decoder info into VideoPlayer\u0027s class definition, or have that be a class that is declared and defined only in VideoPlayer.cpp (VideoPlayerImpl?) (and then, move other members of VideoPlayer into that class that is only accessible from VideoPlayer.cpp).",
      "parentUuid": "0ae75272_8d3b2b6e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 95,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 35
      },
