    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d84eed7_0d524dbd",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 167,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T01:30:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d say the decoding and timing related functions in both VideoPlayer and Decoder are the second top source of confusion to non-ffmpeg-experts. Shouldn\u0027t we take care of all decoding and all timing in separate, single classes?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 167,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 167,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "854111173c42bec9e93fa3db0691749bfa79899a",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8389826a_9e4cd51d",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 167,
      "author": {
        "id": 1128849
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T02:05:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Again, Decoder mainly provides the decodeFrame() function. Originally, I don\u0027t have Decoder class, I thought splitting into a separate class is more readable.\n\nOnce can decode and render in the same thread, however, to do the best a/v sync, we better perform these tasks in separate threads, so they are totally independent. Of course, this increases the locking/waiting exchanges between queues.\n\nFor example, the audio callback doesn\u0027t like any waiting, if we do decoding there, it will cause the whole system not responding. I\u0027ve played so many different versions of the player, starting from a very simple one (400 lines of code), to the current moderate complicatedly version. It\u0027s very involving, and not very easy to understand the code.",
      "parentUuid": "3d84eed7_0d524dbd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 167,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 167,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "854111173c42bec9e93fa3db0691749bfa79899a",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72458179_f3a1a985",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/skin/qt/video-player/VideoPlayer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 27
      },
      "lineNbr": 167,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-12T02:28:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think keeping it in the one class is more readable because we don\u0027t gain much by splitting into different classes; in fact there is more overhead getting the pointer to each class from the other and going back and forth between them duplicating functionality.\n\nI completely agree with decoding and rendering in separate threads though. Thanks for the explanation there.",
      "parentUuid": "8389826a_9e4cd51d",
